<taxonomicName authority="Demange, 1977b: 238" authorityName="Demange" authorityPageNumber="238" authorityYear="1977" box="[151,659,1231,1256]" class="Diplopoda" family="Spirostreptidae" genus="Mardonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spirostreptida" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="importatus">
<emphasis box="[151,401,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Mardonius importatus</emphasis>
<treatmentCitation author="Demange" box="[408,659,1231,1256]" page="238" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" year="1977">
<bibRefCitation author="Demange" box="[408,604,1231,1256]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" refString="Demange, J. - M. (1977 b) Descriptions de trois nouvelles especes de Spirostreptoidea (Myriapodes, Diplopodes) de l'Inde, dont une appartenant a un genre typiquement africain. Bulletin du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, Serie 3, Zoologie, 231, 237 - 242." type="journal article" year="1977" yearSuffix="b">
Demange, 
<number box="[529,588,1231,1256]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="1977.0">1977</number>
b
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number box="[614,659,1232,1256]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="238.241">238</number>
</treatmentCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 241 (D). 
<collectingCountry box="[772,832,1231,1256]" name="India" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">India</collectingCountry>
, Alagarkovil Hills, Bellary Fields. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,269,1268,1293]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Remarks:</emphasis>
This species seems to be the only representative of the primarily Afro- and Neotropical family 
<taxonomicName box="[151,321,1303,1328]" class="Diplopoda" family="Spirostreptidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spirostreptida" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Spirostreptidae</taxonomicName>
that has been recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[667,728,1303,1328]" name="India" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">India</collectingCountry>
. Both other component species of the genus are restricted to central and eastern Africa (cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Krabbe" box="[516,670,1340,1365]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" refString="Krabbe, E. (1982) Systematik der Spirostreptidae (Diplopoda, Spirostreptomorpha). Abhandlungen des Naturwissenschaftlichen Vereins in Hamburg, 24, 1 - 476. [Neue Folge]" type="journal article" year="1982">
Krabbe 
<number box="[610,670,1340,1364]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" value="1982.0">1982</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), whereas 
<taxonomicName box="[797,961,1341,1364]" class="Diplopoda" family="Spirostreptidae" genus="Mardonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spirostreptida" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="importatus">
<emphasis box="[797,961,1341,1364]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">M. importatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has definitely been introduced to 
<collectingCountry box="[1371,1432,1340,1365]" name="India" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">India</collectingCountry>
, although its native area remains unknown.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
